"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810517","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-01-08","<p>Details of Ministerial and senior official meetings are published in the Department’s Quarterly Transparency Returns, which are made publicly available on <a href="http://gov.uk." target="_blank">GOV.UK.</a></p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2018-01-08T15:39:33.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810517/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810517/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810517/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2017-12-21","Chevening Scholarships Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, who the multiple stakeholders within the private sector were at each Chevening business event listed in the Ministerial Meetings section of his Department's Transparency Data for July to September 2017.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","120862"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810518","Northern Ireland Office","false","2018-01-11","<p>The Government is committed to doing all it can to get devolution up and running in Northern Ireland and will outline plans for further talks shortly.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2018-01-11T15:56:20.563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810518/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810518/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810518/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-12-21","Northern Ireland Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, whether he has drawn up a shortlist of independent chairs for potential future talks about restoring the power-sharing Executive in Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Stephen Morgan","Portsmouth South","Stephen Morgan","120863"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810519","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-01-09","<p>Details of Ministerial and senior official meetings are published in the Department’s Quarterly Transparency Returns, which are made publicly available on<a href="http://gov.uk/" target="_blank"> GOV.UK</a>.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2018-01-09T10:49:25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810519/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810519/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810519/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2017-12-21","Department for Exiting the European Union: Departmental Responsibilities","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, who was present at each roundtable discussion listed in the Ministerial Meetings section of his Department's Transparency Data for July to September 2017.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","120864"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810520","Cabinet Office","false","2018-01-25","<p>The Cabinet Office supports the Prime Minister by tracking the delivery of the Government's programme​. This includes working with departments to track the number of looked after children or children subject to child protection or child in need plans.​</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2018-01-25T16:27:23.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810520/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810520/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810520/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-12-21","Children: Social Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, which reports or reviews have been commissioned or conducted by his Department in respect of the number of looked after children or children subject to child protection or child in need plans.","false","Biography information for Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","South Shields","Mrs Emma Lewell-Buck","120865"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810521","Scotland Office","false","2018-01-08","<p>Scotland Office Ministers meet with a range of stakeholders to discuss various issues on a regular basis. The Government publishes a list of all ministerial meetings with external bodies on departmental business on a quarterly basis and are available at gov.uk.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2018-01-08T15:20:15.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810521/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810521/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810521/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-12-21","Scotland Office: Caledonian Media","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, for what reasons Lord Duncan held an introductory meeting with Caledonian Media on 24 August 2017; who he met from that organisation; and what was discussed at that meeting.","false","Biography information for Deidre Brock","Edinburgh North and Leith","Deidre Brock","120866"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810522","Department for International Trade","false","2018-01-09","<p>Following the publication of the Trade White Paper: Preparing for our future UK trade policy, we received 150 responses providing feedback on specific questions posed in the White Paper. In addition, we received a number of responses (7429) as part of a Civil Society campaign. Responses to the questions have been analysed and collated into themes around the key principles as set out in the White Paper. We have made public a summary of the responses we received which was published on 5 January. Views are not attributed to individual respondents or groups of respondents. The Response can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/trade-white-paper-preparing-for-our-future-uk-trade-policy-government-response" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/trade-white-paper-preparing-for-our-future-uk-trade-policy-government-response</a></p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2018-01-09T14:24:56.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810522/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810522/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810522/answer","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810522/answer/previousversion/33123","Biography information for Greg Hands","202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-12-21","Trade Agreements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, pursuant to the Answer of 19 December 2017 to Question 118624, on trade agreements, if he will list the organisations that submitted responses.","false","Biography information for Bill Esterson","Sefton Central","Bill Esterson","120867"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810523","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-01-08","<p>Government assesses all significant new employment regulation on all types of businesses, including micro businesses, through undertaking impact assessments. The Government commissioned Matthew Taylor to conduct an independent review into modern working practices. The review was published in July 2017 and highlighted the strengths of the UK’s flexible labour market relative to other countries. However, the review also proposed new measures the Government should take to improve outcomes for all those participating in the labour market. The Government will respond shortly.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-01-08T16:29:30.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810523/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810523/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810523/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-12-21","Small Businesses: Conditions of Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what recent assessment he has made of the effects of employment regulations on micro-businesses; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Priti Patel","Witham","Priti Patel","120868"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810524","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2018-01-11","<p>No specific assessment has been made of the impact of previous housing targets from the Regional Spatial Strategies regime or other targets introduced before 2010.</p><p>Since 2010, a range of reforms to streamline the planning system have been introduced. This has freed the system of red tape that has stifled it for too long and boosted the building of much-needed homes. This included removing top-down regional planning systems, and enabling communities to have a much greater say in the homes that are built in their area through Neighbourhood Planning. These initiatives are starting to see meaningful results, with 217,000 homes delivered last year and a record number of planning permissions granted.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab","120873","2018-01-11T18:43:00.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810524/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810524/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810524/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-12-21","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment his Department has made of the effect on housing supply of the previous housing targets for local authorities established in the Regional Spatial Strategies.","false","Biography information for Priti Patel","Witham","Priti Patel","120869"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810525","Cabinet Office","false","2018-01-08","<p><em>The changes to regulations affecting business during the 2010-15 Parliament are recorded in Statements of New Regulation that were published every six months. These are available on </em><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/one-in-two-out-statement-of-new-regulation" target="_blank"><em>https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/one-in-two-out-statement-of-new-regulation</em></a><em>.</em></p><p><em>For the 2015-17 Parliament, the Government will shortly publish its final report on the savings to business delivered during that Parliament. </em></p><p><em> </em></p><p><em>For the current Parliament, the Government is committed to maintaining a proportionate approach to regulation to enable business growth while maintaining public protections. This will be monitored through the target that the Government is required to set under the Small Business, Enterprise and Employment Act 2015.</em></p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore","120901","2018-01-08T13:17:07.36Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810525/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810525/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810525/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-12-21","Cabinet Office: Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the title was of each set of regulations introduced by his Department in each month since May 2010; which of those regulations have been (a) subject to the (i) one in one out and (ii) one in two out procedure and (b) (i) revoked and (ii) amended; and what the net cost to (A) the public purse; and (B) business of those regulations is.","false","Biography information for Priti Patel","Witham","Priti Patel","120870"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810526","HM Treasury","false","2018-01-12","<p>The changes to regulations affecting business during the 2010-15 Parliament are recorded in Statements of New Regulation that were published every six months. These are available on <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/one-in-two-out-statement-of-new-regulation" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/one-in-two-out-statement-of-new-regulation</a> .</p><p> </p><p>For the 2015-17 Parliament, the Government will shortly publish its final report on the savings to business delivered during that Parliament.</p><p> </p><p>For the current Parliament, the Government is committed to maintaining a proportionate approach to regulation to enable business growth while maintaining public protections. This will be monitored through the target that the Government is required to set under the Small Business, Enterprise and Employment Act 2015.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick","120902","2018-01-12T14:05:52.783Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810526/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810526/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810526/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-12-21","Treasury: Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the title was of each set of regulations introduced by his Department in each month since May 2010; which of those regulations have been (a) subject to the (i) one in one out and (ii) one in two out procedure and (b) (i) revoked and (ii) amended; and what the net cost to (A) the public purse; and (B) business of those regulations is.","false","Biography information for Priti Patel","Witham","Priti Patel","120871"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810527","Home Office","false","2018-01-12","<p>The changes to Home Office regulations affecting business during the 2010-15 Parliament were recorded in Statements of New Regulation that were published every six months. These are available on <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/one-in-two-out-statement-of-new-regulation" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/one-in-two-out-statement-of-new-regulation</a>. Consolidated information for the period is set out in Annex C to the Ninth Statement of New Regulations.</p><p>In line with its obligations under the Small Business Enterprise and Employment Act 2015, the Government reports on its progress towards achieving the Business Impact Target (BIT). The first BIT report covered the period 8 May 2015 to 26 May 2016. It is available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/530683/bis-16-182-bit-annual-report.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/530683/bis-16-182-bit-annual-report.pdf</a>. The Home Office measures are listed on pages 40 – 41.</p><p>The Government published an interim report for the 2015-2017 Parliament. It is available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/610874/business-impact-target-interim-report-16-17.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/610874/business-impact-target-interim-report-16-17.pdf</a>. The Home Office measures are listed on pages 33 – 35.</p><p>For the 2015-17 Parliament, the Government will publish shortly its final report on the Business Impact Target during that Parliament. The net cost to the public purse is described in the Regulatory Impact Assessments that accompany legislative measures. Regulatory Impact Assessments are available on ‘<a href="http://gov.uk" target="_blank">gov.uk</a>’ and <a href="http://legislation.gov.uk" target="_blank">http://legislation.gov.uk</a>.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-01-12T13:19:54.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810527/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810527/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810527/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-12-21","Home Office: Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the title was of each set of regulations introduced by her Department in each month since May 2010; which of those regulations have been (a) subject to the (i) one in one out and (ii) one in two out procedure and (b) (i) revoked and (ii) amended; and what the net cost to (A) the public purse; and (B) business of those regulations is.","false","Biography information for Priti Patel","Witham","Priti Patel","120872"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810528","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2018-01-11","<p>No specific assessment has been made of the impact of previous housing targets from the Regional Spatial Strategies regime or other targets introduced before 2010.</p><p>Since 2010, a range of reforms to streamline the planning system have been introduced. This has freed the system of red tape that has stifled it for too long and boosted the building of much-needed homes. This included removing top-down regional planning systems, and enabling communities to have a much greater say in the homes that are built in their area through Neighbourhood Planning. These initiatives are starting to see meaningful results, with 217,000 homes delivered last year and a record number of planning permissions granted.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab","120869","2018-01-11T18:43:00.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810528/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810528/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810528/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-12-21","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the quantum of under-supply in housing caused by local authorities pursuing housing supply targets from (a) the Regional Spatial Strategies and (b) other housing targets introduced prior to 2010.","false","Biography information for Priti Patel","Witham","Priti Patel","120873"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810529","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-01-11","<p>The changes to regulations affecting business during the 2010-15 Parliament are recorded in Statements of New Regulation that were published every six months. These are available on https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/one-in-two-out-statement-of-new-regulation.</p><p>For the 2015-17 Parliament, the Government will shortly publish its final report on the savings to business delivered during that Parliament.</p><p>For the current Parliament, the Government is committed to maintaining a proportionate approach to regulation to enable business growth while maintaining public protections. This will be monitored through the target that the Government is required to set under the Small Business, Enterprise and Employment Act 2015.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","120904","2018-01-11T18:15:36.92Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810529/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810529/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810529/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-12-21","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Regulation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what the title was of each set of regulations introduced by his Department in each month since May 2010; which of those regulations have been (a) subject to the (i) one in one out and (ii) one in two out procedure and (b) (i) revoked and (ii) amended; and what the net cost to (A) the public purse; and (B) business of those regulations is.","false","Biography information for Priti Patel","Witham","Priti Patel","120874"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810530","Department for International Trade","false","2018-01-12","<p>The new UK-China bilateral investment fund, of which David Cameron will be Vice-Chairman, is a private sector initiative, and not a government appointment. The fund has not received public money. The Department for International Trade welcomes initiatives which support innovative and sustainable commercial growth opportunities between the UK and China.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2018-01-12T16:32:48.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810530/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810530/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/810530/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-12-21","David Cameron","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, with reference to his Department's factsheet entitled 9th UK China Economic and Financial Dialogue 16 December 2017, whether David Cameron's new role on investment between the UK and China is a Government appointment.","false","Biography information for Mr Philip Hollobone","Kettering","Mr Philip Hollobone","120875"
